## File Structure

```
src/
  app/
    layout.tsx
    page.tsx
    globals.css
  components/
    sections/
      Hero.tsx, SocialProof.tsx, Problem.tsx, HowItWorks.tsx,
      Features.tsx, BeforeAfter.tsx, UseCases.tsx, Testimonial.tsx,
      Pricing.tsx, FAQ.tsx, FinalCTA.tsx, Footer.tsx
    ui/
      Button.tsx, LeverBar.tsx, ScaffoldLine.tsx, Bracket.tsx
  lib/
    constants.ts
```

One section per file. Reusable components in ui/. No prop drilling beyond two levels.

## Component Patterns

### Visual Signature

The Stanzix visual signature is **lever bars and scaffold lines**, not gradients or orbs.

- LeverBar: small horizontal indicator with label + animated bar fill. Used in hero demo and as recurring motif.
- ScaffoldLine: thin amber line with transparent ends, used as section divider, vertical separator, visual flourish.
- Bracket: amber `[ ]` characters wrapping headlines for feature names and key callouts.

Use these three components throughout. They are the brand.

### Buttons

Primary: `bg-accent text-background font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-md hover:bg-accent-hover transition-colors`

Secondary: `border border-accent text-accent font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-md hover:bg-accent/10 transition-colors`

## Voice and Tone for All Copy

- Direct. No marketing fluff. No "revolutionary," "game-changing," "powerful," "seamless."
- Builder-to-builder. Assume reader is technically capable.
- Confident, not arrogant. State what the product does.
- Specific. Numbers over adjectives. "8 levers" beats "powerful customization."
- Active voice always.
- Short sentences. Strong verbs.

## DO NOT

- DO NOT use em dashes or en dashes anywhere. Use periods or commas.
- DO NOT add gradients, glassmorphism, or animated orbs. These are Linear-clone signals.
- DO NOT use Inter font. Use Geist (Inter is the AI tool default we are avoiding).
- DO NOT use stock illustrations, generic AI imagery, or lorem ipsum.
- DO NOT add a light mode toggle in v1. Dark mode only.
- DO NOT over-animate. Restraint is the brand.
- DO NOT use marketing words: revolutionary, game-changing, powerful, seamless, robust, cutting-edge, world-class.
- DO NOT add features I did not ask for. No newsletter modal, no chat widget, no cookie banner, no countdown timer.
- DO NOT use HTML form tags inside React components. Use button onClick handlers.
- DO NOT introduce CSS-in-JS libraries. Tailwind only.
- DO NOT add unused dependencies.

## Animation Guidance

- Section reveals on scroll: subtle fade-in + 8px upward translate, 400ms ease-out, once only.
- Hover states: smooth color or border transitions, no transforms (no scaling, no bouncing).
- Hero lever animations: continuous loop, smooth value transitions every 3-4 seconds.
- Accordion expand: smooth height transition, 250ms ease-out.
- Total animation budget: visitor never waits for an animation to complete.

## Performance Requirements

- Lighthouse Performance: 90+
- First Contentful Paint: under 1.5s
- Largest Contentful Paint: under 2.5s
- No cumulative layout shift after initial load
- font-display: swap on all custom fonts
- Preload Fraunces (used in hero, critical)
- Use next/image for any images
- Code-split heavy sections with dynamic imports

## Accessibility

- WCAG AA minimum
- All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- Visible focus states (amber outline, 2px offset)
- Semantic HTML (use button for buttons, a for links)
- Alt text on all images
- ARIA labels on icon-only buttons
- Sufficient color contrast (verify with WebAIM contrast checker)
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion (disable animations when set)

## Verification Commands

Run after each phase. Fix any errors before continuing.

```bash
npm run build        # Must complete without errors
npm run lint         # Zero warnings
npx tsc --noEmit     # TypeScript clean
```

For the dev server during development:
```bash
npm run dev
```

After deployment:
```bash
npx lighthouse https://stanzix.com --view  # Verify 90+ scores
```

## When in Doubt

- Match the design intent, not just the requirements.
- Restraint over decoration.
- Specific values over conceptual descriptions.
- Read the relevant section spec in stanzix-build-plan.md before building.
- Read copy from stanzix-website-copy.md, do not invent new copy.
- Reference the visual signature (lever bars and scaffold lines) in every section.
